WEBVTT

00:17.184 --> 00:20.855
-[Boyd] Previously on From...
-You feel it? You do?

00:20.938 --> 00:24.775
When I walked inside the ruins,
I think I went somewhere.

00:24.859 --> 00:26.527
You're a Storywalker.

00:26.610 --> 00:29.488
But you can't change a story
once it's been told.

00:29.572 --> 00:31.449
Me and Jade,

00:31.532 --> 00:33.409
we tried to save those children
and set them free.

00:33.492 --> 00:35.578
We've come back
over and over again

00:35.661 --> 00:38.122
because we failed
the first time.

00:38.205 --> 00:39.749
Knowledge comes with a cost.

00:42.460 --> 00:44.462
[gasping]

00:45.171 --> 00:46.756
[Tabitha]
Where's your father?

00:46.839 --> 00:48.132
He's not back yet.

00:48.215 --> 00:50.009
-Wasn't he with you?
-Yeah.

00:50.092 --> 00:51.343
We just got separated.

00:51.427 --> 00:52.928
[tires squealing]

00:53.012 --> 00:54.305
[indistinct chattering]

00:59.518 --> 01:00.853
Sir, can you hear me?

01:00.936 --> 01:02.897
-Dad!
-[Boyd] Okay. Come on, kiddo.

01:02.980 --> 01:04.272
-Dad!
-[Boyd] He's okay.

01:04.355 --> 01:05.483
[Jade]
We need to tell people.

01:05.566 --> 01:07.109
We have no idea
what happened out there.

01:07.193 --> 01:08.486
We don't even know
if it's true.

01:08.569 --> 01:11.489
-You, me, Jim--
-Jim's not home.

01:11.572 --> 01:14.241
Put that down.
She's here to help.

01:14.325 --> 01:16.202
Sara took his eye out
with a screwdriver.

01:16.285 --> 01:18.037
-Can you stitch him up?
-[Acosta] I got you.

01:18.120 --> 01:20.664
Once the baby was born,
we were supposed to go home.

01:20.748 --> 01:21.999
That's okay.
We got you. I got you.

01:22.082 --> 01:23.501
You think you're
some kind of hero?

01:23.584 --> 01:25.544
What you did
to that kid up there,

01:25.628 --> 01:27.670
you're a fucking monster.

01:30.257 --> 01:31.842
[exhales heavily]

01:31.926 --> 01:34.094
You played
a very special role

01:34.178 --> 01:36.931
in a very important story.

01:37.890 --> 01:39.308
I couldn't come
to them as I was.

01:39.390 --> 01:40.559
[groans]

01:40.643 --> 01:42.186
Not with everything
they learned.

01:43.938 --> 01:45.021
Are you all right?

01:45.104 --> 01:46.106
I'm lost.

01:47.942 --> 01:49.109
[gasping]

01:49.193 --> 01:50.902
[tires squealing]

01:50.985 --> 01:53.697
I'm sorry you won't be here
to see what comes next.

01:53.781 --> 01:55.533
It's always
my favorite part.

01:55.616 --> 01:58.494
This is when they
tear themselves apart.

01:59.829 --> 02:01.580
[muffled choking]

02:18.848 --> 02:20.057
Hey, Sophia?

02:30.234 --> 02:31.527
Sophia?

02:31.610 --> 02:33.320
[weeping hysterically]

02:33.404 --> 02:35.990
[weeping]

02:36.073 --> 02:38.075
No. No, no, no, no, no.

02:38.158 --> 02:39.326
Sophia!

02:39.410 --> 02:41.745
[weeping hysterically]

02:41.829 --> 02:43.747
Hey, hey.

02:43.831 --> 02:45.666
Hey. Okay.
Come back inside. Okay?

02:45.749 --> 02:47.501
-No, I can't.
-We need to get back inside!

02:47.585 --> 02:48.961
I can't go back
in there, please.

02:53.716 --> 02:55.134
Kenny?

02:57.720 --> 02:58.596
Okay. Get inside!

03:02.099 --> 03:03.434
Hey! Hey!

03:03.517 --> 03:05.936
-[door locking]
-What'd I tell you?

03:06.020 --> 03:08.105
I told you, you don't
go outside! I told you!

03:08.188 --> 03:09.398
He's dead.

03:11.984 --> 03:13.027
What?

03:13.110 --> 03:15.863
My-- My father died.

03:15.946 --> 03:17.114
-[sobbing]
-Oh.

03:17.197 --> 03:19.199
[sobbing]

03:19.283 --> 03:20.743
Okay, okay. I'm sorry.

03:20.826 --> 03:22.077
I'm sorry. But okay.

03:22.161 --> 03:24.914
Okay, I didn't--
you don't go outside, okay?

03:24.997 --> 03:26.332
I didn't mean to.
I just...

03:26.415 --> 03:27.541
I'm sorry.

03:27.625 --> 03:29.501
Hey, what's going on?

03:29.585 --> 03:31.503
-[sobbing] He's gone.
-It's okay, it's okay.

03:31.587 --> 03:33.923
I don't know what now.
He's gone.

03:34.006 --> 03:36.675
-[sobbing]
-[Kenny] Shh, shh, shh.

03:36.759 --> 03:38.469
[sobbing continues]

03:38.552 --> 03:40.638
[Kenny] I'm sorry,
but you don't go outside, okay?

03:40.721 --> 03:42.348
We're gonna take care
of you now, okay?

03:42.430 --> 03:44.475
[sobbing]

03:51.607 --> 03:52.608
[door opens]

04:00.783 --> 04:01.784
Boyd?

04:04.954 --> 04:07.039
Uh...

04:07.122 --> 04:08.874
would you step
back inside for a minute?

04:11.460 --> 04:13.629
[Elgin stammers]

04:33.232 --> 04:35.985
What I'm about
to say is not for me.

04:37.987 --> 04:40.072
It's for everyone here.

04:42.282 --> 04:44.909
If people
find out what happened,

04:44.994 --> 04:48.122
if people
find out what you did,

04:48.205 --> 04:51.125
what we did...

04:51.207 --> 04:52.835
that's the kind of thing

04:52.918 --> 04:54.837
that could tear
this place apart.

04:57.089 --> 04:58.882
And I can't let that happen.

05:01.510 --> 05:04.596
So, if anybody asks,

05:04.680 --> 05:06.807
and they will ask...

05:08.851 --> 05:11.103
you're gonna tell them
that you lost your eye

05:11.186 --> 05:13.188
trying to help Fatima.

05:16.692 --> 05:17.651
And if I don't?

05:19.653 --> 05:20.487
[thudding]

05:22.406 --> 05:24.867
Then I will tell everyone
that you killed Tillie.

05:26.910 --> 05:29.913
And then,
I'ma put you in the box.

05:29.997 --> 05:31.582
You understand
what that means, right?

05:33.751 --> 05:34.918
Right?

05:39.423 --> 05:40.382
Good.

05:52.144 --> 05:54.104
They're gonna find out.

05:55.731 --> 05:56.940
One way or another,

05:57.024 --> 05:59.026
the truth
always comes out.

06:01.737 --> 06:05.741
Well, if I was you...
I would make sure it doesn't.

06:23.634 --> 06:25.010
[tuning, static hissing]

06:25.094 --> 06:27.054
[rooster crowing]

06:27.137 --> 06:28.639
[alarm ringing]

06:28.722 --> 06:31.100
["Good Morning Good Morning"
by playing]

06:31.183 --> 06:34.394
♪ Good morning, good morning,
good morning, good morning ♪

06:34.478 --> 06:36.396
♪ Good morning ♪

06:36.480 --> 06:41.276
♪ Nothing to do to save
his life, call his wife in ♪

06:41.360 --> 06:42.861
♪ Nothing to say ♪

06:42.945 --> 06:47.366
♪ But "What a day,
how's your boy been?" ♪

06:47.449 --> 06:50.159
♪ Nothing to do,
it's up to you ♪

06:50.244 --> 06:54.498
♪ I've got nothing to say
but it's okay ♪

06:54.581 --> 06:58.502
♪ Good morning,
good morning, good morning ♪

06:58.585 --> 07:03.465
♪ Going to work don't wanna go,
feeling low down ♪

07:03.549 --> 07:07.594
♪ Heading for home, you start
to roam, then you're in town ♪

07:09.429 --> 07:11.265
♪ Everybody knows
there's nothing doing ♪

07:11.348 --> 07:13.183
♪ Everything is closed,
it's like a ruin ♪

07:13.267 --> 07:15.144
♪ Everyone you see
is half asleep ♪

07:15.227 --> 07:18.772
♪ And you're on your own,
you're in the street ♪

07:18.856 --> 07:21.775
♪ After a while
you start to smile ♪

07:21.859 --> 07:23.819
♪ Now you feel cool ♪

07:23.902 --> 07:28.615
♪ Then you decide to take
a walk by the old school ♪

07:29.741 --> 07:32.703
♪ Nothing has changed,
it's still the same ♪

07:32.786 --> 07:36.665
♪ I've got nothing to say
but it's okay ♪

07:36.748 --> 07:38.959
♪ Good morning, good morning,
good morning... ♪

07:39.042 --> 07:43.881
[tense music plays]

07:54.558 --> 07:59.479
["Que Sera, Sera (Whatever Will
Be, Will Be)" playing]

08:04.443 --> 08:09.323
♪ When I was just a little boy ♪

08:09.406 --> 08:11.742
♪ I asked my father ♪

08:11.825 --> 08:13.368
♪ "What will I be?" ♪

08:15.495 --> 08:17.873
♪ "Will I be handsome?" ♪

08:17.956 --> 08:20.292
♪ "Will I be rich?" ♪

08:20.375 --> 08:24.338
♪ Here's what he said to me ♪

08:24.421 --> 08:27.257
♪ Que sera sera ♪

08:28.634 --> 08:31.803
♪ Whatever will be will be ♪

08:33.472 --> 08:37.558
♪ The future's not ours to see ♪

08:37.643 --> 08:40.354
♪ Que sera sera ♪

08:42.648 --> 08:45.525
♪ What will be will be ♪

08:54.993 --> 08:59.790
♪ Now I have
children of my own ♪

08:59.873 --> 09:02.292
♪ They ask their father ♪

09:02.376 --> 09:05.963
♪ "What will I be?" ♪

09:06.046 --> 09:08.465
♪ "Will I be pretty?" ♪

09:08.548 --> 09:10.884
♪ "Will I be rich?" ♪

09:10.968 --> 09:13.303
♪ I tell them tenderly ♪

09:14.972 --> 09:17.516
♪ Que sera sera ♪

09:19.101 --> 09:22.271
♪ Whatever will be will be ♪

09:24.106 --> 09:28.026
♪ The future's not ours to see ♪

09:28.110 --> 09:30.529
♪ Que sera sera ♪

09:33.198 --> 09:36.076
♪ What will be will be ♪

09:38.412 --> 09:41.206
♪ Que sera sera ♪

09:54.469 --> 09:59.308
[foreboding music plays]

10:03.312 --> 10:04.521
[people chatter]

10:16.575 --> 10:19.453
[foreboding music continues]

10:21.830 --> 10:22.914
No, God, no.

10:22.998 --> 10:24.833
Oh, God.

10:24.916 --> 10:26.626
Oh, God.
[breathing shakily]

10:27.753 --> 10:28.628
No, no, no, no.

10:29.796 --> 10:32.341
No, no, no, no.

10:32.424 --> 10:34.593
-No, no...
-What's that?

10:37.888 --> 10:39.348
-Mom, what is that?
-Hey.

10:39.431 --> 10:40.891
-Inside!
-No, Mom! What is that?!

10:40.974 --> 10:42.351
-What's in the bag?
-I don't know.

10:42.434 --> 10:44.227
-What happened?
-Nothing. It's okay.

10:44.311 --> 10:45.437
Mom!

10:45.520 --> 10:47.522
Ethan! Come on!

10:47.606 --> 10:48.815
Ethan! No, no, no, no, no!
Ethan!

10:48.899 --> 10:50.067
-No, no, no! Hey!
-Is that my--

10:50.150 --> 10:51.860
-Ethan! No, no, no, whoa!
-Is that my dad?

10:51.943 --> 10:53.111
-Hey, no.
-Is my dad in there?

10:53.195 --> 10:54.237
Hey, everything's okay.

10:56.448 --> 10:57.991
-[Boyd] Hey, look...
-Mom?

10:58.075 --> 11:00.577
-Okay? Everything is okay.
-You shouldn't be here, honey.

11:00.660 --> 11:02.704
[Ethan] It's not him, right?
It's not him!

11:02.788 --> 11:05.499
Hey, hey, hey, hey.
Listen to me, okay?

11:05.582 --> 11:07.167
You're gonna go--

11:07.250 --> 11:08.960
You're gonna go
with your sister.

11:09.044 --> 11:10.629
You're gonna go down
to the barn, okay?

11:10.712 --> 11:12.130
You're gonna check
on the animals.

11:12.214 --> 11:13.799
-No, no!
-Yes. Please, please, Julie.

11:13.882 --> 11:15.133
-It's not him, right?
-Listen...

11:15.217 --> 11:16.802
-[Ethan] It's not him.
-...Listen to me.

11:16.885 --> 11:18.261
-Julie, please.
-No.

11:18.345 --> 11:20.389
I need you to go out
to the barn with Ethan.

11:20.472 --> 11:22.516
I need you to be brave.

11:22.599 --> 11:24.393
Can you do that?

11:24.476 --> 11:26.353
Okay. Take him. Okay.

11:26.436 --> 11:28.063
[Boyd] Just try to breathe.
Look at me.

11:28.146 --> 11:29.481
Ethan,
we're gonna go for a walk.

11:29.564 --> 11:31.149
It's not him!
We'll go find him, right?

11:31.233 --> 11:33.068
It's okay, it's okay. Come on.
Come on, please.

11:33.151 --> 11:35.153
-We'll find him! Right?
-Come on.

11:43.161 --> 11:45.580
[breathing heavily]
Tabitha.

11:45.664 --> 11:47.457
-Oh, my God, Boyd.
-Tabitha.

11:47.540 --> 11:49.418
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

11:49.501 --> 11:52.337
[exhaling sharply]
Get it down.

11:52.421 --> 11:53.588
[Boyd] Okay.

11:53.672 --> 11:56.425
Just...
Hey, Jade.

12:05.058 --> 12:08.353
It's not him, right?
We need to go find him.

12:09.896 --> 12:12.232
Julie?

12:12.315 --> 12:14.234
We're gonna find him, right?

12:15.944 --> 12:17.821
We're gonna find him.

12:19.489 --> 12:20.824
You promise?

12:28.165 --> 12:29.124
Okay.

12:30.375 --> 12:31.585
[grunts]

12:31.668 --> 12:34.045
-[Jade] I got it.
-[Boyd] Okay.

12:34.129 --> 12:37.549
[tense music plays]

12:46.308 --> 12:47.684
[Boyd] Nice and easy.

12:50.896 --> 12:52.814
Okay.

13:05.327 --> 13:09.372
[breathing shakily]

13:17.339 --> 13:18.340
Okay.

13:18.423 --> 13:19.299
Stop.

13:25.096 --> 13:27.057
[breathing shakily]

13:44.282 --> 13:45.200
[breathing shakily]

13:51.039 --> 13:51.957
[whimpers]

13:57.045 --> 13:58.421
[breathing shakily]

14:01.758 --> 14:03.343
[crowd chattering quietly]

14:11.685 --> 14:13.687
[screaming]

14:13.770 --> 14:15.313
[townspeople chattering]

14:15.397 --> 14:18.024
[woman] What is it?

14:18.108 --> 14:19.568
[Tabitha] Oh, my God.

14:21.861 --> 14:24.281
[sobbing]

14:25.782 --> 14:28.743
[Julie continues sobbing]

14:28.827 --> 14:31.621
No, no, no. Hold.
Hold. No, no. Come here.

14:31.705 --> 14:33.456
-No!
-Come here, come here.

14:33.540 --> 14:37.627
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God. No.

14:39.087 --> 14:40.755
Oh, no!

14:40.839 --> 14:42.048
Oh, Jim.
[sobbing]

14:42.132 --> 14:44.676
Oh, no, no, no.

14:44.759 --> 14:49.681
[sobbing]

14:49.764 --> 14:51.641
[sobbing continues]

14:51.725 --> 14:53.518
Hey, hey.

14:55.103 --> 14:57.022
[sobbing]

14:57.105 --> 15:00.734
[wailing]
Oh, my God!

15:00.817 --> 15:04.696
[sobbing]

15:04.779 --> 15:08.241
[sobbing continues]

15:17.959 --> 15:20.253
[sobbing]

15:20.337 --> 15:23.548
[sobbing continues]

15:23.632 --> 15:28.345
Why?
Why did they do that to him?

15:28.428 --> 15:32.474
Why?
[sobbing]

15:42.942 --> 15:45.236
[sniffling]

15:45.320 --> 15:47.030
[breathing shakily]

15:48.323 --> 15:51.951
[sniffling]

15:52.035 --> 15:53.411
Thank you.

15:54.996 --> 15:58.165
Yeah. Uh, of course.

16:06.633 --> 16:08.718
[sniffling]
What happens now?

16:11.346 --> 16:13.973
Um...

16:14.057 --> 16:17.143
Well, I'll-- I'll talk
to Boyd about a burial.

16:17.227 --> 16:18.978
Who's Boyd?

16:19.062 --> 16:20.438
He's the sheriff.

16:20.522 --> 16:23.942
He's the one that helped
get you out of the car.

16:24.025 --> 16:25.694
He seemed kind.

16:27.654 --> 16:31.366
He is. He is.
He's, uh...

16:31.449 --> 16:33.785
He's kinda the thing that holds
this whole place together.

16:39.249 --> 16:40.917
[breathing shakily]

16:43.586 --> 16:44.796
Hey, if you want,

16:44.879 --> 16:47.590
we could take
a walk down into town.

16:47.674 --> 16:49.509
You know, I could show you
around a little bit,

16:49.592 --> 16:52.345
and, uh... maybe get you
a spare set of glasses

16:52.429 --> 16:53.596
from the storage room.

16:53.680 --> 16:55.432
I'd like that
very much, thank you.

16:55.515 --> 16:56.599
[sniffling]

16:56.683 --> 16:58.351
Okay.

16:59.811 --> 17:01.271
[Ethan]
I hate it here!

17:01.354 --> 17:03.523
I hate this place!

17:03.606 --> 17:05.733
-I don't wanna be here anymore!
-Hey! Ethan! Ethan!

17:05.817 --> 17:07.068
You need to stop, okay?

17:07.152 --> 17:09.362
What did you do?
Why didn't he come home?

17:09.445 --> 17:10.864
I did nothing!

17:10.946 --> 17:14.032
You're lying! You're a liar!

17:14.117 --> 17:16.953
You guys always fight!

17:17.036 --> 17:20.290
I want Dad! I hate it here!
And I hate you!

17:20.373 --> 17:22.040
Please...

17:24.210 --> 17:25.753
We didn't fight!

17:27.422 --> 17:28.798
It doesn't matter.

17:30.258 --> 17:33.511
[sobbing]

17:33.595 --> 17:35.555
I'm...
[sobbing]

17:39.601 --> 17:41.311
-[Boyd] You got it?
-[Jade] Yeah, I got it.

17:41.394 --> 17:42.395
One sec.

17:54.115 --> 17:55.992
[Boyd grunting]

18:02.916 --> 18:03.875
[grunts]

18:07.629 --> 18:10.465
I'm gonna go check
on Tabitha and the kids.

18:12.258 --> 18:13.968
-I'm good.
-[Jade] Okay.

18:17.972 --> 18:19.265
Dad.

18:22.352 --> 18:24.145
I'm gonna need some help.

18:25.230 --> 18:26.147
Okay?

18:27.690 --> 18:29.067
Yeah, okay.

18:29.150 --> 18:30.026
Okay.

18:32.028 --> 18:36.866
[mournful music plays]

18:57.262 --> 18:58.763
[Jade]
Up.

18:58.847 --> 19:00.390
[Boyd]
All right?

19:00.473 --> 19:01.641
[grunting]

19:01.724 --> 19:03.101
It's okay.

19:03.184 --> 19:04.727
[grunting]

19:13.903 --> 19:15.196
All good?

19:15.280 --> 19:16.990
All the way to the end.

19:18.908 --> 19:21.286
[grunting]

19:33.339 --> 19:35.758
We need to clean him up before
Tabitha and the kids see him.

19:38.177 --> 19:39.554
[Boyd] Yeah.

19:44.225 --> 19:46.603
"Knowledge comes at a cost."

19:49.272 --> 19:51.190
The fuck does that even mean?

19:54.569 --> 19:55.904
We need to talk.

20:06.581 --> 20:07.749
Sara?

20:09.417 --> 20:11.502
Sara, what's...?

20:11.586 --> 20:13.588
What's going on?

20:13.671 --> 20:16.925
They found Jim
in the barn this morning.

20:21.596 --> 20:23.473
Is he, um...

20:27.977 --> 20:29.312
Uh...

20:29.395 --> 20:32.065
Um...
[clears throat]

20:32.148 --> 20:35.860
I'm gonna-- I'm gonna need you
to head back up to the clinic.

20:35.944 --> 20:38.154
But-- But you said
we'd get new glasses.

20:40.239 --> 20:41.866
Are you going
to the storage room?

20:43.242 --> 20:44.202
Yeah.

20:44.285 --> 20:45.244
Uh...

20:45.328 --> 20:46.496
I can take her.

20:47.914 --> 20:49.248
No. Um...

20:49.332 --> 20:51.542
You're Sophia, right?

20:51.626 --> 20:52.961
I'm Sara.

20:53.044 --> 20:54.170
I used to work at the diner.

20:54.253 --> 20:56.047
I know where
all of the good stuff is.

21:00.718 --> 21:02.637
[stammers] Okay. Yeah.

21:04.013 --> 21:06.391
I know you two were close.

21:06.474 --> 21:08.267
I'm sorry.

21:14.565 --> 21:15.900
Come on.

21:20.530 --> 21:23.700
[pensive music plays]

21:30.081 --> 21:32.083
[Jade] The children,

21:32.166 --> 21:35.294
the seven kids,
they kept saying this...

21:35.378 --> 21:40.091
word, over and over again:
"Anghkooey."

21:40.174 --> 21:42.343
[Boyd] Okay.

21:42.427 --> 21:44.721
When we played
the song at the tree,

21:44.804 --> 21:47.640
it was like
something... unlocked,

21:47.724 --> 21:49.934
and we finally
understood.

21:50.018 --> 21:51.227
Anghkooey...

21:52.437 --> 21:55.773
...it means 'remember',

21:55.857 --> 21:57.442
and we did.

21:59.777 --> 22:03.031
"Knowledge
comes at a cost"?

22:03.114 --> 22:05.533
That's why they wrote it.

22:07.618 --> 22:09.704
They killed Jim
because of us.

22:10.830 --> 22:13.833
"If we push too hard,
something would push back."

22:15.418 --> 22:16.794
What's that?

22:16.878 --> 22:20.423
Something Sara said once.
We were out in the woods.

22:20.506 --> 22:23.801
Her brother, he had
a theory about this place.

22:23.885 --> 22:26.804
He didn't think looking
for answers was a good idea.

22:26.888 --> 22:27.764
[exhales]

22:29.432 --> 22:30.892
So, what do we do now?

22:33.352 --> 22:35.480
Assuming you're right,
that you and Tabitha

22:35.563 --> 22:37.857
have been coming back here
over and over and over,

22:37.940 --> 22:41.277
that these kids keep
calling you back to help them,

22:41.360 --> 22:42.904
how do we do it?

22:44.155 --> 22:47.366
I mean, how do you even begin
to save something that's...

22:47.450 --> 22:49.202
already dead?

22:49.285 --> 22:51.204
I don't know.

22:52.747 --> 22:54.165
I'm working on it.

22:54.248 --> 22:55.833
Yeah.

22:55.917 --> 22:57.710
Work harder.

22:59.921 --> 23:00.838
Come on.

23:03.549 --> 23:04.759
[door opens]

23:09.222 --> 23:10.223
[door closes]

23:16.437 --> 23:17.396
[door closes]

23:17.480 --> 23:20.108
-Give me a second.
-Mm-hmm.

23:24.445 --> 23:25.446
Hey.

23:28.407 --> 23:30.409
Are you all right?

23:30.493 --> 23:31.994
We're not friends.

23:33.621 --> 23:35.206
Don't talk to me
like we're friends.

23:38.042 --> 23:38.960
Okay.

23:44.173 --> 23:46.676
It's right through here.
Come on.

24:10.116 --> 24:11.117
Ethan?

24:20.168 --> 24:24.964
[thoughtful music plays]

24:47.778 --> 24:49.405
Julie?

24:53.492 --> 24:54.952
Where's my mom?

24:55.036 --> 24:57.496
Uh, she'll be back.

24:57.580 --> 25:00.583
She just had to, uh,
step out for a minute.

25:01.792 --> 25:02.877
Can I get you something?

25:02.960 --> 25:04.670
I'm going for a walk.

25:04.754 --> 25:07.256
I want someone
to go with you.

25:07.340 --> 25:09.467
It's the middle
of the day, Donna.

25:09.550 --> 25:12.511
I'll be fine.
I-I just need to...

25:12.595 --> 25:14.555
Okay.

25:14.639 --> 25:17.266
Uh, Ethan's asleep.

25:17.350 --> 25:19.393
[Donna] Julie?

25:19.477 --> 25:22.355
If you need anything...

25:22.438 --> 25:24.440
you just ask me, okay?

25:37.536 --> 25:38.621
Randall?

25:40.373 --> 25:43.167
[exhaling sharply]

25:43.251 --> 25:44.460
Randall!

25:44.543 --> 25:47.004
What the hell do you want?

25:47.088 --> 25:49.340
[breathing shakily]

25:49.423 --> 25:51.884
Hey, what happened?

25:53.552 --> 25:55.137
My dad is...

25:58.266 --> 26:00.309
[exhaling sharply]
Jesus Christ.

26:03.312 --> 26:04.897
Hey, look,
I'm-- I'm sorry.

26:04.981 --> 26:06.190
No, don't, don't.

26:08.567 --> 26:09.777
I need your help.

26:12.613 --> 26:14.198
Yeah. Okay.

26:14.282 --> 26:17.868
I need you to come back
to the ruins with me.

26:17.952 --> 26:19.578
Why?

26:19.662 --> 26:21.455
Because
I'm gonna save him.

26:29.588 --> 26:30.881
[Randall] Julie?

26:34.010 --> 26:37.388
[indistinct muttering]

26:41.809 --> 26:44.103
[door opens]

26:48.816 --> 26:51.068
Tabitha?

26:51.152 --> 26:53.237
[breathing shakily]

26:53.321 --> 26:54.697
Get out.

26:54.780 --> 26:56.991
-No, listen, please, I just--
-I said get out!

26:59.869 --> 27:02.079
This means it's real.

27:02.163 --> 27:04.373
The memories,

27:04.457 --> 27:08.210
everything
they showed us,

27:08.294 --> 27:09.712
it's real.

27:10.838 --> 27:11.839
It is real.

27:15.843 --> 27:17.303
I don't give a shit.

27:17.386 --> 27:20.973
Do you understand?
I don't fucking care.

27:21.057 --> 27:23.392
Look, I can't even imagine
what you're going through.

27:23.476 --> 27:25.394
I know you don't want
to hear this right now,

27:25.478 --> 27:27.146
but what they did,

27:27.229 --> 27:30.649
this message,

27:30.733 --> 27:33.736
I think they're doing it to
stop us from digging further.

27:33.819 --> 27:36.030
They're trying
to make us afraid.

27:36.113 --> 27:37.698
Well, then, it worked...

27:42.787 --> 27:45.081
...because
I'm fucking terrified.

27:47.500 --> 27:50.086
My husband's dead.

27:50.169 --> 27:51.879
Do you understand?

27:51.962 --> 27:55.091
My husband's dead.

27:55.174 --> 27:57.718
You have to think
about your children now.

27:57.802 --> 27:59.136
[scoffs]

28:01.389 --> 28:03.224
Know what?

28:03.307 --> 28:04.725
Fuck you.

28:06.102 --> 28:08.062
Fuck you!

28:08.145 --> 28:09.480
What do you know? Huh?

28:09.563 --> 28:11.690
What do you know?

28:11.774 --> 28:14.026
Do you wanna go back
to the Bottle Tree

28:14.110 --> 28:16.278
and play your stupid violin?

28:17.780 --> 28:19.865
Because you've got
nothing to lose.

28:21.158 --> 28:23.744
Because you don't give a shit
about anybody but yourself.

28:26.414 --> 28:28.040
That is not true.

28:31.836 --> 28:33.587
It should have been you...

28:35.381 --> 28:37.758
hanging from the fucking rafter.

28:39.760 --> 28:41.220
It should have been you.

29:01.407 --> 29:02.575
Fuck it.

29:24.305 --> 29:26.557
[engine revving]

29:26.640 --> 29:28.851
Hey!

29:28.934 --> 29:30.769
Fuck.

29:30.853 --> 29:32.897
Hey, hey! Whoa!

29:32.980 --> 29:34.231
Turn it off!

29:34.315 --> 29:36.150
Fuck!

29:36.233 --> 29:39.445
Turn off the engine
and get out of the ambulance.

29:39.528 --> 29:40.988
No, look! Don't!

29:41.071 --> 29:42.656
Babe!

29:42.740 --> 29:44.950
Are you insane? Get the fuck
outta the ambulance!

29:45.034 --> 29:47.745
You wanna go for a ride?
I'm coming with you.

29:48.829 --> 29:50.372
-Jesus Christ!
-It's okay. It's okay.

29:50.456 --> 29:51.749
-Get out, Kristi.
-It's okay.

29:53.083 --> 29:54.293
Fine.

29:56.045 --> 29:57.963
[Marielle] Hey! Stop!

30:05.387 --> 30:06.597
Kenny.

30:09.767 --> 30:11.685
I, uh, heard about Jim.

30:14.647 --> 30:15.898
Yeah.

30:16.982 --> 30:20.736
They left us a message
this time? That's new.

30:20.819 --> 30:23.906
Yeah. Jade has
a theory about that.

30:23.989 --> 30:26.116
Sure.
Everybody's got a theory.

30:26.200 --> 30:27.910
No, there might be
something to this one.

30:29.245 --> 30:31.038
Boyd!

30:31.121 --> 30:32.540
Kristi's in trouble.

30:32.623 --> 30:34.500
-What?
-Acosta took the ambulance.

30:34.583 --> 30:35.834
She's got Kristi inside.

30:35.918 --> 30:37.711
[Marielle breathing heavily]

30:45.344 --> 30:46.971
A tad big.

30:47.054 --> 30:49.431
Okay. Um...

30:52.268 --> 30:54.311
Oh, no. Those do not work.

31:00.901 --> 31:02.486
How about these?

31:02.570 --> 31:04.321
Those look good.

31:06.865 --> 31:10.244
So, um...
it's so sad.

31:10.327 --> 31:12.997
All these--
All these things, they, uh--

31:13.080 --> 31:15.082
they belonged to people
that were trapped here?

31:17.751 --> 31:18.669
Yeah.

31:21.338 --> 31:25.050
I wonder who these belonged to.

31:25.134 --> 31:27.511
Um, it's kind of nice though.

31:27.595 --> 31:30.848
I mean, there's a part
of them that's still here,

31:30.931 --> 31:32.182
a part that's...

31:32.266 --> 31:34.852
-[string twanging]
-...not forgotten.

31:34.935 --> 31:37.563
I've never really
thought of it that way.

31:44.445 --> 31:45.404
[gasps]

31:47.197 --> 31:49.908
What happened
this morning to that man?

31:51.952 --> 31:54.580
Does that sort of thing
happen a lot?

31:54.663 --> 31:56.999
It never used to.

31:57.082 --> 31:59.752
For a long time,
after Boyd found the talismans,

31:59.835 --> 32:02.129
things were...

32:02.212 --> 32:04.673
It happens
a lot more often now.

32:08.802 --> 32:10.137
I'm sorry.

32:10.220 --> 32:12.014
I-- I shouldn't
have said that.

32:12.097 --> 32:13.849
It's-- it's okay.

32:13.932 --> 32:16.060
It's important
to be honest about things.

32:16.143 --> 32:19.355
Um, my dad used to
always say that.

32:23.734 --> 32:26.028
Do you have family here?

32:27.404 --> 32:29.406
No.

32:29.490 --> 32:32.618
Not anymore.

32:32.701 --> 32:34.036
[exhaling sharply]

32:37.498 --> 32:42.002
Uh, you must be hungry.
We should get some food.

32:42.920 --> 32:45.756
Yeah, I am.
I'm-- I'm starving.

32:45.839 --> 32:47.466
Come on.

32:51.679 --> 32:56.475
[ominous music plays]

33:06.193 --> 33:09.321
[engine revving]

33:09.405 --> 33:11.699
What the fuck?

33:11.782 --> 33:15.327
[vehicle accelerating]

33:18.205 --> 33:19.498
Here they come. Look.

33:19.581 --> 33:20.791
[engine revving]

33:20.874 --> 33:23.585
Hey! Hey! Wait! Wait!

33:26.213 --> 33:27.756
What's going on?

33:27.840 --> 33:30.551
Acosta's got Kristi
in the ambulance!

33:30.634 --> 33:32.302
Where the fuck
are they going?

33:34.930 --> 33:37.474
[woman] What are they doing?

33:37.558 --> 33:39.435
-[Boyd] Goddamn it, Acosta.
-[Donna] What the hell?

33:39.518 --> 33:40.936
[Boyd] All right.

33:54.450 --> 33:56.201
So, everyone says
there's no way out, right?

33:56.285 --> 33:58.704
You just go round and round.
Well, I didn't.

33:58.787 --> 34:01.415
The night I got here, we drove
in, we stopped in the road,

34:01.498 --> 34:04.668
and then everything just...
it all fucking exploded,

34:04.752 --> 34:06.754
and then I took all
of you at your word.

34:06.837 --> 34:08.922
Why should I believe
a single thing you people say?

34:10.966 --> 34:13.802
Look, is this about Elgin?
Look, you need to understand--

34:13.886 --> 34:16.346
No, I don't need to
understand shit, all right?

34:16.429 --> 34:18.056
[sighs]
Fuck, you're a doctor!

34:18.139 --> 34:20.768
You're supposed to help people.
You're really okay with that?

34:20.851 --> 34:22.811
Oh, I'm not okay
with any of this.

34:22.895 --> 34:24.563
And you're a cop,

34:24.646 --> 34:26.648
and what you're doing
is gonna get people hurt.

34:26.732 --> 34:29.610
No. What I'm doing
is getting out,

34:29.693 --> 34:31.862
right fucking now.

34:31.945 --> 34:33.906
[engine revving]

34:36.116 --> 34:37.159
[Randall] Julie.

34:38.702 --> 34:41.246
Julie, slow down.
Slow down.

34:42.831 --> 34:45.167
So, what? We step inside
the ruins, and then what?

34:45.250 --> 34:47.168
I mean,
walk through time?

34:47.252 --> 34:48.670
Ethan called it Storywalking.

34:48.754 --> 34:50.964
Okay, great. That doesn't
make it any fucking better!

34:51.047 --> 34:52.800
-Look, Julie, stop! You can't--
-What?

34:55.010 --> 34:57.554
Like, what happened...

34:57.638 --> 35:00.182
with your dad,

35:00.265 --> 35:02.100
what you're going
through right now...

35:02.184 --> 35:05.604
Hey, you gotta take a breath.

35:06.939 --> 35:08.106
And what?

35:10.067 --> 35:12.569
What do I do then? Huh?

35:12.653 --> 35:15.405
I am telling you,

35:15.489 --> 35:17.783
when I walked into those ruins,
I went somewhere.

35:17.866 --> 35:22.204
Okay? And if I did it once,
I can do it again.

35:22.287 --> 35:24.915
Even if there
is the slightest fucking chance,

35:24.998 --> 35:28.502
I have to try. Please.

35:33.841 --> 35:37.094
Just tell me
what you need me to do.

35:39.471 --> 35:42.182
[door creaking]

36:16.758 --> 36:18.969
[breathing unsteadily]

36:27.019 --> 36:29.271
Why didn't
you come home, Jim?

36:30.564 --> 36:32.316
[sniffling]

36:32.399 --> 36:34.276
I was waiting for you.

36:35.736 --> 36:38.030
Why didn't you come home?

36:42.618 --> 36:44.578
I'm so angry at you.

36:48.123 --> 36:49.958
All night, I thought about

36:50.042 --> 36:52.294
what I wish
I'd said to you in the woods.

36:52.377 --> 36:53.253
[sniffling]

36:56.715 --> 36:58.383
I thought about
the fact that...

37:01.678 --> 37:05.098
I have loved you since
the first moment I saw you.

37:12.648 --> 37:16.318
There's been so much
fighting and so much pain.

37:16.401 --> 37:19.738
[sniffling]

37:19.821 --> 37:21.531
You were still my person.

37:26.703 --> 37:28.121
You were my everything,

37:28.205 --> 37:30.624
and I'm so afraid
you didn't know that.

37:37.839 --> 37:40.509
How am I supposed to do
this without you here?

37:50.143 --> 37:52.396
[sniffling]
We're gonna be okay.

37:55.941 --> 37:57.734
Julie and Ethan...

37:59.861 --> 38:03.198
I don't know how,

38:03.281 --> 38:05.117
but I'm gonna find a way
to take care of them,

38:05.200 --> 38:07.077
to keep them safe.

38:08.662 --> 38:10.580
You don't have to be afraid.

38:12.040 --> 38:14.209
[sniffling]

38:22.342 --> 38:24.219
I love you, Jim.

38:30.350 --> 38:31.518
Goodbye.

38:36.606 --> 38:38.358
Just-- Oh, here we go.

38:38.442 --> 38:40.110
Hey, get--
get out of the way.

38:41.820 --> 38:42.946
Hey, stop!

38:46.658 --> 38:47.743
Slow down.

38:47.826 --> 38:48.744
Stop!

38:50.746 --> 38:51.663
Slow dow-- slow down!

38:51.747 --> 38:52.748
Stop! Stop!

38:55.375 --> 38:56.585
Hey, Acosta!

38:56.668 --> 39:00.297
[whooshing]

39:00.380 --> 39:02.090
Fuck! You're going way
too fucking fast right now!

39:02.174 --> 39:04.468
We've been through town twice.
What more do you need to see?

39:04.551 --> 39:06.511
There's gotta be a way!
I'm not gonna just sit around

39:06.595 --> 39:08.680
and wait for those things
to pick us off one by one.

39:08.764 --> 39:10.307
You guys just hang
your rocks at night.

39:10.390 --> 39:12.517
You pretend you're safe,
thinking that Sheriff Boyd

39:12.601 --> 39:13.935
is gonna what,
somehow save you?

39:14.019 --> 39:15.270
Let me tell you
something, Boyd?

39:15.353 --> 39:16.855
Boyd doesn't know
what he's doing.

39:16.938 --> 39:18.982
None of you people know
what the fuck you're doing.

39:19.066 --> 39:20.233
But you do?

39:20.317 --> 39:21.610
Yeah, well,
at least I'm trying.

39:23.612 --> 39:26.198
-That was a lot faster.
-Yeah, that's the pattern.

39:26.281 --> 39:27.616
If she's looking
for a way out,

39:27.699 --> 39:30.118
she's just gonna
get more and more...

39:30.202 --> 39:32.954
-What do we do?
-Get the strip.

39:33.038 --> 39:34.039
Yeah.

39:37.209 --> 39:38.418
Victor?

39:40.796 --> 39:42.672
You in here?

39:53.892 --> 39:55.769
[Victor] You shouldn't
have come here.

40:03.902 --> 40:05.779
Hey, I, uh...

40:05.862 --> 40:08.657
[stammering]
I heard about Jim.

40:08.740 --> 40:10.492
I'm sorry.

40:10.575 --> 40:13.120
You shouldn't--
you shouldn't have come here.

40:13.203 --> 40:15.789
You should never
have come to this place.

40:17.124 --> 40:18.875
Uh...

40:18.959 --> 40:21.670
Have you gone
to see, uh, Ethan yet?

40:21.753 --> 40:23.421
-No!
-No? No, okay.

40:23.505 --> 40:26.007
No. I can't.

40:26.091 --> 40:28.218
You can't?

40:28.301 --> 40:30.428
Well, Victor, he's--
he's your friend,

40:30.512 --> 40:34.057
and-- and he needs you,
so when you're ready...

40:34.141 --> 40:37.102
No.
Those words on the wall...

40:37.185 --> 40:38.478
The words, sure, yeah.

40:38.562 --> 40:41.898
You see,
it takes everything good.

40:41.982 --> 40:46.403
It takes everything...
everything good away.

40:46.486 --> 40:49.197
And then, what if--
what if t takes you next time?

40:50.532 --> 40:53.285
Me? What?
I'm not going anywhere.

40:53.368 --> 40:54.995
No, no!

40:56.580 --> 40:57.706
You don't know that.

40:57.789 --> 40:59.166
No.

40:59.249 --> 41:00.625
You don't know that.

41:00.709 --> 41:01.835
Okay.

41:01.918 --> 41:03.587
So, you just
shouldn't have come.

41:03.670 --> 41:05.463
[stammering]

41:05.547 --> 41:07.924
You shouldn't have
come to this place.

41:08.008 --> 41:09.926
You should never have--
never have come.

41:10.010 --> 41:11.469
Hey, hey, hey, hey.
Listen.

41:11.553 --> 41:15.682
No one should have
come to this place.

41:15.765 --> 41:18.268
Hey, right? None of us.

41:18.351 --> 41:21.771
But, you know, we're here,
you and me,

41:21.855 --> 41:23.565
and we're together.

41:23.648 --> 41:26.568
I'll take that
any day of the week,

41:26.651 --> 41:29.321
no matter what gets written
on the-- on the walls.

41:29.404 --> 41:32.657
We-- we face
this together.

41:32.741 --> 41:35.994
Okay? Okay?

41:46.796 --> 41:51.509
So, you just...
walk inside?

41:51.593 --> 41:52.636
Yeah.

41:53.929 --> 41:55.972
And then what?

41:56.056 --> 41:57.682
Then I find my dad.

42:02.187 --> 42:03.355
You go first.

42:03.438 --> 42:04.606
What?

42:04.689 --> 42:06.608
Just walk inside.

42:06.691 --> 42:09.027
-Why?
-Will you just do it, please?

42:15.408 --> 42:20.121
[ominous music plays]

42:28.505 --> 42:30.507
What's supposed to happen?

42:30.590 --> 42:32.384
Nothing.

42:32.467 --> 42:35.220
I-- I-- I just had to make sure
that the same thing

42:35.303 --> 42:37.806
wasn't going to happen to you
when you come in to get me.

42:37.889 --> 42:38.807
Come back.

42:42.310 --> 42:44.729
Look, look,

42:44.813 --> 42:47.649
I need you to give me some time
before you pull me out.

42:47.732 --> 42:51.403
Okay?
Even if it looks bad.

42:51.486 --> 42:52.946
What do you mean
"if it looks bad"?

42:55.573 --> 42:57.742
-Julie, what's gonna happen?
-Promise me?

42:57.826 --> 42:59.202
Please.

42:59.286 --> 43:01.705
Okay, fine.

43:01.788 --> 43:02.998
You have to promise.

43:05.041 --> 43:06.793
-Promise!
-All right, yes.

43:06.876 --> 43:08.586
-I promise.
-Okay.

43:18.221 --> 43:22.976
[ominous music plays]

43:41.703 --> 43:45.081
[creature screaming]

44:12.692 --> 44:14.402
[creature screaming]

44:19.783 --> 44:21.534
Dad!

44:28.666 --> 44:30.627
[Boyd] Well, you guys,
let's get out of here. Go!

44:30.710 --> 44:33.129
Go! Go!

44:34.047 --> 44:36.716
[gun firing]

44:38.551 --> 44:39.427
[gun firing]

44:41.304 --> 44:42.222
Dad!

44:45.392 --> 44:47.602
[groans]

44:49.729 --> 44:52.107
[straining]

44:52.190 --> 44:53.566
Get off of me!

44:53.650 --> 44:55.777
But I want to play.

44:55.860 --> 45:00.281
[grunting]

45:03.451 --> 45:04.577
Come on. Come on.

45:04.661 --> 45:07.872
Randall!

45:07.956 --> 45:09.290
Randall, pull me out!

45:09.374 --> 45:11.418
There's no one here to help you.

45:11.501 --> 45:12.460
No!

45:14.421 --> 45:15.505
[screeching]

45:15.588 --> 45:17.674
[screams]

45:24.139 --> 45:26.349
I got you. I got you.

45:26.433 --> 45:28.184
No, no, no, no, no!

45:28.268 --> 45:30.186
Hey, hey, hey. Shh. Shh.
Look at me. Look at me.

45:30.270 --> 45:31.688
Look at me. Breathe.
You're okay.

45:31.771 --> 45:33.815
I saw him. Oh, Randall!

45:33.898 --> 45:36.151
Oh, my God! I saw him!
I saw him and...

45:36.234 --> 45:37.527
-I have to go back!
-No, no, stop.

45:37.610 --> 45:40.071
No, no, no.
Hey, stop, stop, stop.

45:40.155 --> 45:41.448
-I've got you.
-[sobbing]

45:41.531 --> 45:43.783
-I have to go back!
-I know.

45:52.041 --> 45:53.334
Ethan?

45:56.337 --> 45:58.006
Ethan, can I come in?

46:00.216 --> 46:01.134
Ethan?

46:05.013 --> 46:09.642
[ominous music plays]

46:11.227 --> 46:13.730
Donna?

46:13.813 --> 46:15.148
Ethan's not up there.

46:15.231 --> 46:18.985
What?
I was here the whole time.

46:19.068 --> 46:20.111
Ethan!

46:20.195 --> 46:22.155
Tabitha, he was upstairs!

46:22.238 --> 46:23.364
Ethan!

46:29.621 --> 46:30.955
Ethan!

46:33.791 --> 46:36.377
-Perfect. You got it?
-Yeah.

46:37.504 --> 46:38.671
Hey, she's gonna be okay.

46:47.263 --> 46:49.807
My mom, she, uh...

46:49.891 --> 46:52.435
she always
believed in hell.

46:52.519 --> 46:54.479
But you know what I think?

46:54.562 --> 46:56.022
I think hell is for people

46:56.105 --> 46:59.317
who think that they deserve
to suffer, and I don't.

46:59.400 --> 47:02.195
I'm a good person,
and I don't deserve be here.

47:02.278 --> 47:03.905
None of us
deserve to be here.

47:03.988 --> 47:06.074
I don't know that. I don't.

47:06.157 --> 47:08.284
I don't know a single thing
about you people.

47:08.368 --> 47:11.079
And, you know, maybe the real
reason that you don't try harder

47:11.162 --> 47:14.415
is that, deep down, you think
that you deserve to be here.

47:14.499 --> 47:16.751
The real reason we don't
try harder is because,

47:16.834 --> 47:18.920
every time we do,
someone fucking dies.

47:19.003 --> 47:20.797
Do you know how many people
I've known

47:20.880 --> 47:23.633
who thought they knew
exactly what this place is,

47:23.716 --> 47:26.135
how many theories I've listened
to on why we're all here,

47:26.219 --> 47:28.263
or brilliant ideas
of how to get out?

47:28.346 --> 47:30.682
You wanna know what
they all have in common?

47:30.765 --> 47:32.100
They're all fucking dead.

47:32.183 --> 47:34.477
There is no way out.
Do you understand that?

47:34.561 --> 47:37.981
No! Okay? There's a way!

47:38.064 --> 47:40.608
There's a way!
There's always a way.

47:46.739 --> 47:47.991
Ethan.

47:56.749 --> 47:58.251
Okay, pull over.

48:01.879 --> 48:03.590
He's fine.

48:03.673 --> 48:05.633
He's a fucking kid in the woods
whose father just died.

48:05.717 --> 48:06.593
Pull over.

48:15.351 --> 48:17.145
No, no, no, no, no.

48:18.062 --> 48:19.480
-Hey. Come on, Marielle.
-Okay.

48:19.564 --> 48:20.857
Let's go.
Let's go. Let's go.

48:20.940 --> 48:22.108
Fuck.

48:22.191 --> 48:23.985
[tires screeching]

48:24.068 --> 48:25.695
-Stop!
-[tires screeching]

48:29.907 --> 48:31.367
[Marielle] Kristi!

48:31.451 --> 48:33.328
Are you okay?

48:33.411 --> 48:35.246
Hey! You get the fuck out
of the car!

48:35.330 --> 48:37.165
Get the fuck out!

48:37.248 --> 48:38.833
-[Kenny] Hey, you good?
-Ow. Yeah.

48:38.916 --> 48:42.045
What the fuck
is wrong with you? Huh?

48:42.128 --> 48:44.714
You could've killed somebody,
you know that? Turn around.

48:48.176 --> 48:51.179
Fucking driving like a crazy
fucking person out here.

48:52.847 --> 48:55.600
Huh? Answer me!

48:55.683 --> 48:56.392
Boyd!

49:06.527 --> 49:08.029
[Boyd] Let's go. Let's go.

49:08.112 --> 49:10.073
-[Kristi] Ethan.
-What?

49:10.156 --> 49:12.367
Ethan. He was walking
on the road.

49:12.450 --> 49:13.534
-[Boyd] What?
-Yeah.

50:16.472 --> 50:17.765
Dad?

50:20.435 --> 50:21.978
Ethan.

50:27.900 --> 50:29.736
[exhaling sharply]

50:32.905 --> 50:34.574
What are you
doing out here?

50:34.657 --> 50:36.492
I came to get the radio.

50:36.576 --> 50:37.827
[exhaling sharply]

50:41.914 --> 50:43.374
It's broken.

50:43.458 --> 50:46.377
I thought maybe I could
send Thomas a message,

50:46.461 --> 50:49.213
the real Thomas,

50:49.297 --> 50:53.134
that he should look for you
so you wouldn't be alone.

51:00.641 --> 51:01.976
What's wrong?

51:03.394 --> 51:05.021
Everything's okay.

51:06.689 --> 51:08.524
Do you remember
what I told you

51:08.608 --> 51:10.610
last time we were here
at the RV?

51:10.693 --> 51:13.571
That when bad things happen,

51:13.654 --> 51:16.741
we have to look after each other
and always do our best?

51:17.825 --> 51:19.786
That's right.

51:19.869 --> 51:22.830
And your mom and your sister,

51:22.914 --> 51:26.209
they need that from you now,
more than ever.

51:28.628 --> 51:30.338
You're not staying, are you?

51:33.966 --> 51:35.843
I wish that I could.

51:40.348 --> 51:44.143
Dad, what's happening?

51:44.227 --> 51:46.938
[emotional music plays]

51:48.773 --> 51:52.735
I need you
to do something very important.

51:52.819 --> 51:54.320
The night we arrived here,

51:54.403 --> 51:56.739
when we crashed the RV
and we were trapped inside...

52:00.535 --> 52:02.745
you had a dream.

52:03.746 --> 52:07.291
Do you remember
what you dreamt about?

52:07.375 --> 52:09.544
Lake of Tears?

52:09.627 --> 52:11.254
That's right.

52:11.337 --> 52:13.714
Do you know why?

52:16.759 --> 52:20.304
It's here,
and I need you to find it.

52:21.889 --> 52:24.100
Why can't we find it together?

52:24.183 --> 52:26.060
-[Tabitha] Ethan!
-[gasps]

52:30.314 --> 52:31.274
[Tabitha] Ethan!

52:34.694 --> 52:36.946
Dad?

52:37.029 --> 52:38.823
Dad, where are you?

52:38.906 --> 52:40.658
-Ethan!
-Dad, come back!

52:40.741 --> 52:42.493
-Dad, please come back!
-Ethan, Ethan!

52:44.537 --> 52:47.415
Oh, baby. Why are you here?
I was so worried.

52:47.498 --> 52:50.793
I saw Dad.
He was right here.

52:52.545 --> 52:54.589
Oh, my baby.

53:04.765 --> 53:11.647
♪ ♪
